<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 12:40AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON EST TODAY...
A widely scattered wintry mix of freezing rain and sleet have
started to fill in across the Tri-Cities and northern Thumb.
Temperatures now range between 30 to 32 degrees and are forecasted
to stay at or below freezing through the mid morning hours. This
will allow precipitation to freeze on contact on untreated
roadways and surfaces. Drivers are urged to prepare for icy roads
and pedestrians should be prepared for icy paved surfaces.</description>
